      "question": "If $\\tan A = \\frac{4}{3}$, find the value of $\\sin A + \\cos A$.",
      "answer": "7/5",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use the definition of tangent in a right-angled triangle to find the hypotenuse.",
          "Calculate sin A and cos A and sum them."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\text{Given } \\tan A = \\frac{P}{B} = \\frac{4}{3}. \\text{ Let } P=4k, B=3k. \\text{ By Pythagoras theorem, } H = \\sqrt{(4k)^2 + (3k)^2} = 5k. \\sin A = \\frac{4}{5}, \\cos A = \\frac{3}{5}. \\sin A + \\cos A = \\frac{4}{5} + \\frac{3}{5} = \\frac{7}{5}."
      },
