      "question": "If $3 \\cot \\theta = 2$, find the value of $\\frac{4 \\sin \\theta - 3 \\cos \\theta}{2 \\sin \\theta + 6 \\cos \\theta}$.",
      "answer": "1/3",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Find $\\cot \\theta = 2/3$.",
          "Divide numerator and denominator by $\\sin \\theta$ to express in terms of $\\cot \\theta$ and substitute."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\cot \\theta = \\frac{2}{3}. \\text{Expression} = \\frac{\\frac{4 \\sin \\theta}{\\sin \\theta} - \\frac{3 \\cos \\theta}{\\sin \\theta}}{\\frac{2 \\sin \\theta}{\\sin \\theta} + \\frac{6 \\cos \\theta}{\\sin \\theta}} = \\frac{4 - 3 \\cot \\theta}{2 + 6 \\cot \\theta}. \\text{Substitute } \\cot \\theta = \\frac{2}{3}: \\frac{4 - 3(2/3)}{2 + 6(2/3)} = \\frac{4-2}{2+4} = \\frac{2}{6} = \\frac{1}{3}."
      },
